Name: ADAMS
column16: I1) The modeling technology supports collaborative modeling, i.e., it allows multiple stakeholders to manage, collaborate, and be aware of each others’ work on a set of shared models representing key aspects of the same system.
I2) The modeling technology is publicly available (either as an open-source or commercial product).

Name: ADEPT2
column16: I3) The documentation of the modeling technology is publicly available.

Name: ADM
column16: E1) The modeling technology does not explicitly address/support collaborative modeling, e.g., Eclipse EMF, MPS, ATL, Epsilon, etc.

Name: ADOxx
column16: E2) The modeling technology is not available for download as a binary that can be run on current operating systems from an official website or an affiliated platform supporting it (e.g., a GitHub repository).

Name: AMENITIES
column16: E3) The documentation of the modeling technology is not in English.

Name: TOGAF
Rationale: , TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture Framework) is not a model-driven engineering (MDE) tool. TOGAF is a framework for enterprise architecture that provides a set of principles, best practices, and standard methods for designing, planning, implementing, and governing the architecture of an enterprise.

Name: This paper proposes a framework for synchronous and asynchronous concurrent and collaborative modeling.
